							<br><p>Peanuts (Arachis hypogaea) are thought to have originated in South America, where they thrive in tropical and subtropical 
							climates (American Peanut Council, 2020). The name “peanut” is misleading, because it is not botanically a nut, but rather a legume
							(a member of the pea and bean family). 
							The edible seeds of a peanut plant start above ground but mature underground; thus peanuts are also known as groundnuts (National 
							Peanut Board, 2021).</p>
							<br><p><b><u>Global peanuts Producers</u></b></p>
							<ol>
							<li>China</li>
							<li>India</li>
							<li>Nigeria</li>
							<li>Sudan</li>
							<li>Burma</li>
							</ol><br><br>
